description:
// O C C A S I O N
- Dinner with the boyfriend after school.

// F O O D
- Bulgolgi: thinly sliced and sweet. The portion is small, good enough for one.
- Seafood sundubu (Spicy): wasn't spicy at all! Definitely had tastier sundubu before, but this sufficed. I finished the bowl because I was so famished and realized that all the taste sunk to the bottom (mix your sundubu jjigae well!).

// S E R V I C E
- Staff is pretty attentive. It may be that there wasn't that many people that day.

// O T H E R
- Very clean enviornment.
- Right next to a Korean Market if you want an attempt at making better food than My Tofu House!
